    <!-- How It Works Section -->
    <section id="how-it-works" class="content-section text-center">
        <div class="download-section">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="col-lg-8 col-lg-offset-2">
                    <h2>How It Works</h2>
                    <p>Foretoken's algorithm is based on a simple linear regression model, as shown below:</p>
                    <p class="formula"><img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foretoken/formula-a.png"><br>
                    <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foretoken/formula-b.png"><br><br>
                    <img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foretoken/formula-c.png"></p>
                    <p>Foretoken makes this much easier to accomplish without the need for Excel or SPSS. Here's a walkthrough on how to get going:</p>
                    <img class="walkthrough" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foretoken/screenshot1"><p class="caption">First, create a new project. In our case, we've created one called "Iraq GNI per capita (USD)."</p>
                    <img class="walkthrough" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foretoken/screenshot2"><p class="caption">Next, we input our data for Historical Period (x), which we enter as years in our case, and Historical Data (y), which we enter as GNI or Gross National Income per capita in USD (source: <a href="http://data.worldbank.org/">World Bank</a>).
                    The columns and rows in gray simply show the math for the regression model. These fields are uneditable.</p>
                    <img class="walkthrough" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foretoken/screenshot3"><p class="caption">In the second table, we enter the periods that we would like to forecast, in our case the years 2014 through 2016. Click on "Show Results" to display the graph and forecasted data.</p>
                    <img class="walkthrough" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foretoken/screenshot4"><p class="caption">Voila! We have our results. The blue line represents the regression model or trend line. The white line represents both our historical and forecasted data.</p>
                    <img class="walkthrough" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/foretoken/screenshot5"><p class="caption">The table below the graph contains the forecasted periods and their corresponding data points.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

